  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Training on strategic water management for governmental institutions in Peru (Part 2)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective of the project is to strengthen the capacity of the governmental water institutions in Peru for the implementation of a long-term strategic water management approach in the country and through a long-term partnership between the Netherlands and Peru (Blue Deal). This project will benefit the Peruvian community by means of a safer, environmentally friendly and efficient water management, which guarantees better water supply. Through the implementation of integrated watershed management, flooding of populated areas can be prevented. Peru has had a history with natural disasters as a result of the El Ni&#xF1;o weather phenomenon. In 2017, a large scale flood struck northern Peru, a particularly vulnerable area of the country. Peruvian authorities have since been working on an Integrated Water Resource Management plan. The Netherlands is ideally positioned to provide Peru technical and institutional support and capacity building, resulting in a more resilient and sustainable plan for water management. Exploratory talks between the relevant Peruvian and Dutch counterparts will be held at Expo Agua 2018, Peru&#x2019;s most important water fair.De Blue Deal is a new programme of the Dutch Water boards, together with the Ministries of Foreign Affairs and Infrastructure and Water. The goal is to to help 20 million people in 40 basins to have access to clean, sufficient and safe water worldwide.Check www.uvw.nl/thema/internationaal/blue-deal/ for more information about Blue Deal.</narrative>
  </description>
